					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you don't have too many objects and they don't have many variables, you can have linear layout using lda $nnnn,x addressing. Say, you can have 16 objects max, each uses 16 bytes, or 32 objects, 8 bytes each - 256 bytes total. You can use $PP0n offsets to access individual variables of an object (PP is page for the list, n is offset in the object), and X contains object number*size of object.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />My stuff at <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/shiru8bit" class="postlink">YouTube</a>, <a href="http://soundcloud.com/shiru" class="postlink">SoundCloud</a></div>
